One of the better Dunkins in the borough-- maybe the city! Spacious & comfortable. Quick service, lovely people. Perfectly conceived and executed.  The breakfast sandwiches do not disappoint, and the donuts are official Dunkins. The egg and cheese was a melting glory, and the home fries were crisp. The coffee, I think, is better cold at Dunkins-- if you're looking for a quick cup of hot joe, head to a bodega for something better, but if you're in the ices business-- Dunkins!
